>>d6ac485e-1feb-43a2-8f9f-9226de2692de
Zeronet can't cuck us. It's not like they can purge the board off their servers like f-droid, because it isn't on their servers. If they push an update blocking the board you just don't install it until there's an uncucked fork.
The real danger for this board is spambots (that's what killed USENET) and just growth beyond what the protocols can support.

>>59029966-f1c1-4b49-9550-3aab62524c23
Wrong. It's set to "Enable" but that doesn't provide protection, it needs to be set to "Always".
